  "body": "Hello, \r\nI have came across the issue that the keyword delete is not working for mapping and array in remix, so I have tried to find why it is. \r\n\r\nIn fact, if you put 0 into the mapping or array that has already values, it will get an error. \r\n\r\nFor example, \r\n// array has 3 values\r\nuint[] public array = [97,98,99];\r\n// if I put 0 into the first index of the array, it will return an error\r\narray[1] = 0; // error. \r\n\r\n// mapping \r\nmapping(string => uint) public map;   \r\n//Not Error since it does not have any value yet other than default value 0\r\nmap[\"a\"] = 0 \r\n\r\n// Once the key set up the specific value \r\nmap[\"a\"] = 3;\r\n//it wiill get an error from map[\"a\"] = 0 \r\nmap[\"a\"] = 0 \r\n\r\n\r\nplease try this code in remix, ( this code is totally working in truffle)\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0\r\npragma solidity >=0.7.0 <0.9.0;\r\n\r\ncontract SimpleEx {\r\n\r\n    uint[] public array = [97,98,99];\r\n     \r\n    function updateArrayZero(uint _index) public {\r\n        array[_index] = 0;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function deleteArray(uint _index) public {\r\n       delete array[_index];\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    mapping(string => uint) public map;   \r\n    function Key_A_get_0() public {\r\n        map[\"a\"] = 0;\r\n    }\r\n    function Key_A_get_3() public {\r\n        map[\"a\"] = 3;\r\n    }\r\n    function delete_Key_A() public {\r\n        delete map[\"a\"];\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n ",
